main event: Eight objects were tracked on radar and observed visually over West Branch, Michigan, on November 29, 1959.
interesting points: Objects were visually spaced and tracked on ground radar,Observations noted the objects merging and breaking apart,Radar tracks fluctuated,The objects were initially thought to be reflections in red tower lights but were later assumed to be elliptical in shape,The sighting lasted for 5 minutes and the objects were described as moving at great speed.
witness description: No witnesses confirmed as the report indicated no other observers identified.
